ENTRY            F0640   20251217   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0640001   20251217   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 11         23
TITLE      Resonance spectroscopy of 44Ti in the excitation
           energy range 9.05 to 10.28 MeV
AUTHOR     (A.Chatterjee,S.Kailas,S.Saini,S.K.Gupta,M.K.Mehta)
INSTITUTE  (3INDTRM)
REFERENCE  (J,ZP/A,317,209,1984)
FACILITY   (VDG,3INDTRM)
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Four surface barrier detectors were used to
           detect the scattered particles at the laboratory angles
           of 85,125,141 and 165 degr.
SAMPLE     Targets were prepared by the vacuum evaporation of
           natural CaF2 (96.92% 40Ca) on thin carbon film backings
            (~8 ug/cm2). The total target thickness used was
           about 5 keV at 4 MeV alpha particle energy
METHOD     (BCINT)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T,,6.) The total error on the average comprising
           of errors in:
            * Statistical error (~3%)
           (ERR-1) Uncertainty due to the normalising constants;
           (ERR-2) Uncertainty due to the target nonuniformity
ADD-RES    The data was analysed in terms of the R matrix theory.
HISTORY    (20030915C)
           (20251217U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
            ANALYSIS -> ADD-RES.
ENDBIB              23
COMMON               3          3
EN-ERR     ERR-1      ERR-2
KEV        PER-CENT   PER-CENT
        20.         4.         3.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           30
SUBENT        F0640002   20251217   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  4          4
REACTION   (20-CA-40(A,EL)20-CA-40,,DA)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical error
STATUS     (CURVE,,A.Chatterjee+,J,ZP/A,317,209,1984) Fig.2
HISTORY    (20251217U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB               4
COMMON               2          3
EN-ERR-DIG ERR-DIG
MEV        MB/SR
      0.004        3.0
ENDCOMMON            3
DATA                 4       1000
